30 Years Burning Down The Road is a project that commemorates the 30th anniversary of the edition of Born In The U.S.A., the album that launched Springsteen to stardom and consolidated him in the business of music.

This box set contains two books, three CDs and three DVDs. The DVDs include the live interpretation of all the songs that were recorded during the sessions of the album, in the own Born In The U.S.A. Tour and through these thirty years.

For the entire project visit springsteencorner.com (in spanish).

Thanks to TheLonely for having the idea of this project and trust me to do this part. Thanks to him also for his translations, they have helped me very much to do the subtitles. Thanks to brucebase.wikispaces.com for the transcriptions of great part of the speeches that appear in this work. And finally thanks to all the people who shares Springsteen's material in jungleland.dnsalias.com.
